5: What is the meaning of this?
9: Hmm? What are you talking about?
14:
I found this... present laying in front
of my door earlier this morning.
17:
Of all the people in Starview Village,
only you would be willing to do
something like this, Alk.
20:
Uh... I didn't put that present there,
Adonis!
23:
Then who did? There was no sender
written anywhere I could see. This
is... quite ominous.
27:
Ominous?! It's a present someone
obviously wanted you to have!
31:
I've had packages sent to me
multiple times before—and it has
never been a pleasant experience.
Do you know what they contained?
34:
Piles of tangled human hair, stained
and tattered stuffed animals, and
even house keys—with an address
written on them.
41:
Well. I'd like to believe such things
wouldn't happen in Starview Village.
Time to see what's in the box.
43:
...If it does end up being hair, I'd
appreciate it if you could dispose of
it for me.
48:
Can we not talk about boxes full of
human hair? I'm cooking right now!
Besides, I'm sure it won't be that.
51:
Let's hope so.
Here we go...
59:
...A younger me would have wanted
one just like this.
70:
I see. It seems a grand conspiracy
was afoot... You're all more cunning
than I gave you credit for.
75:
H-hey, it's not like I lied to you! It
wasn't me who placed the present
on your doorstep!
79:
I see... Caught out on an utterly
boring technicality.
84:
Come on, it was all in good fun.
Though, uh, we didn't know about
your complicated history with
presents.
87:
Yeah, sorry about that. We just
wanted to surprise you, but we
accidentally brought up some
unpleasant memories...
92:
Pay no heed to it.
But I must ask... Why go through all
the trouble?
97:
It was my idea. I... How do I put this.
I wished to apologize for my
previous behavior.
106:
What's this, all of a sudden? If
anything, I'm at fault for making you
worry about me so much.
113:
And while I think the concept of
"family" doesn't work for me... I am
willing to call you friends.
116: I see. Then that is what we shall be!
120:
I have to admit though, seeing this
wood carving made me chuckle.
Was this your idea too, Light?
124:
Y-yes. I consulted Alk and Stella on
the matter, but it was my decision.
127: I-is it not to your liking?
130:
I know I may appear young, but I'm
not nearly so juvenile as to jump for
joy when I'm given a playtoy.
133: ...But I suppose I don't dislike it.
136:
I might even say that this is the
present I didn't realize I needed all
along.
138:
Regardless, thank you.
I will cherish it.
143:
You're welcome! And yes, I would be
grateful if you did so.
148:
All right, 'nuff sentimental stuff. Time
to party it up! I could really go for
some meat right about now.
153: And cake. I want to eat cake.
158:
We definitely have cake! I mean, we
WILL—'cause I'm baking it right now!
163:
In that case, perhaps I could be of
help.
168: Wait, really? That would be great!
171:
Okay, in that case, could I ask you to
whip up a nice meringue out of
these egg whites?
175:
...I retract my previous statement.
This is a matter best left to the
hands of experts. I'll wait here
patiently instead.
